        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 4:29PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Madison, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Strong wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Strawn, Hartford, Gridley, and John Redmond Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
